704580f-c.text:
(1)
Fulton Street, at the N.W. corner of Georgia Ave., showing M. and A. Bookman's drygoods,, clothing and shoe store which was established at this location in 1852.  In 1874 it moved to Jamaica and Georgia Aves.  It was no longer in business in 1908.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, showing also the Fulton Street Elevated lines of the
B.M.T.

April 1929.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3)
The same, another view east on Fulton Street.

April 1929.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

704615f-a.text:
Georgia Ave., east side, south of Fulton Street.  In the background is the Long Island R.R. structure.  In the left foreground (No. 33) is the Wartburg Chapel (Lutheran).

April 1929.
